ai_summary: Jim Tullis was an American politician who served in the Florida House of Representatives and the Jacksonville City Council. Born in 1941, he was known for his contributions to local governance and public service in Florida. Tullis held office in the Florida House from 1974 to 1982, representing parts of Duval County. He passed away in 2023, leaving behind a legacy of civic engagement and legislative work.

Allan Bense was an American politician born in 1947, best known for serving as the Speaker of the Florida House of Representatives from 2004 to 2006. A member of the Republican Party, he played a key role in shaping Florida's legislative policies during his tenure. Bense was also a successful businessman, co-founding a real estate development company before entering politics. He passed away in 2014 after a battle with cancer, leaving a legacy in Florida's political history.
